TIPS

-> excel adds col to the left of the selected col...toh joh col ko right click karke drop down mein insert choose kiya hai
uske left side pe insert hogi col

-> if u need to add more number of rows or col just select that many number of rows or col and then do right click and insert

-> Woh cell range mein dollar symbol laane ke liye use F4

###################
UPPER AND LOWER CASE
=LOWER(Mention the cell address which you want to change)
=UPPER(Mention the cell address which you want to change)

###################
SELECTING ENTIRE ROWS OR COLS

Click on the col name like E, D or whatever ......shortcut - Ctrl + SpaceBar
Click on the row name like 3,4,6 or whatever......shortcut - Shift + SpaceBar

If you want to select the entire col but only those cell having data then - Ctrl + Shift + Page Down
If you want to select the entire row but only those cell having data then - Ctrl + Shift + Right/Left arrow Key


##################
CONDITIONAL FORMATTING

Present under Home - Styles - Conditional Formatting
Used to pass on a condition and then decide what to do with the cell

-> comparing 2 cells
=IF(Cell add 1 = Cell add 2, "Match","Not Mached")

=VLOOKUP(lookup_value,table_array,col_index_number,range_lookup)
VLOOKUP compares the lookup_value to the values of the col specified in the range specified

=IFERROR(VLOOKUP(lookup_value,table_array,col_index_number,range_lookup),"Not Found")
Using IFERROR we can specify that if element is not found what message can be printed

If we need to compare Ford and Ford India , as both are same but it may give not found as answer so we use wildcard symbol - "*"
=VLOOKUP(lookup_value&&"*",table_array,col_index_number,range_lookup)


##################
CONVERTING ROWS TO COLUMNS
Ctrl+ C to copy while pasting go to "paste specials" option and then choose transpose
or
=TRANSPOSE(select_the_table_array)

##################
SELECTING EMPTY ROWS OR BLANK ROWS

Home - Find and select - go to specials - blanks - delete
